IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE SCOPE OF OUR PRIMARY MEDICAL SERVICES IS FOCUSED ON MAINTAINING ACCESS TO COMPREHENSIVE PRIMARY AND PREVENTATIVE HEALTHCARE IN ORDER TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH STATUS OF UNDERSERVED AND VULNERABLE POPULATIONS. THE PRIMARY SERVICE AREA IS NORTH AND NORTHEAST MINNEAPOLIS WITH NW HENNEPIN COUNTY AND SOUTHERN ANOKA COUNTY AS SECONDARY SERVICE AREAS. THE TARGET POPULATION INCLUDES LOW-INCOME PEOPLE, BOTH UNINSURED AND THOSE ON MEDICAID. SERVICES ARE PROVIDED AT THREE FREESTANDING CLINICS: FREMONT CLINIC IN NORTH MINNEAPOLIS, CENTRAL AVENUE CLINIC AND SHERIDAN WOMEN & CHILDREN'S CLINIC IN NORTHEAST MINNEAPOLIS. ON-SITE SERVICES INCLUDE PRIMARY CARE, PREVENTION, OUTREACH, OB/GYN, CHRONIC DISEASE, INTERPRETING, AND ASSISTANCE WITH HEALTH CARE PLAN ENROLLMENT. WE PROVIDE REFERRALS AND CARE COORDINATION FOR DENTAL, MENTAL HEALTH AND SUBSTANCE ABUSE, HOSPITAL, AND SPECIALTY SERVICES THROUGH PARTNERSHIPS WITH OTHER COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF NEIGHBORHOOD HEALTHSOURCE IS TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH OF OUR COMMUNITIES BY PROVIDING QUALITY HEALTH CARE SERVICES THAT ARE AFFORDABLE AND ACCESSIBLE.
IRS990.Desc: PRIMARY MEDICAL CARE:THE SCOPE OF OUR PRIMARY MEDICAL SERVICES IS FOCUSED ON MAINTAINING ACCESS TO COMPREHENSIVE PRIMARY AND PREVENTIVE HEALTHCARE IN ORDER TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH STATUS OF UNDERSERVED AND VULNERABLE POPULATIONS. THE PRIMARY SERVICE AREA IS NORTH AND NORTHEAST MINNEAPOLIS WITH NW HENNEPIN COUNTY AND SOUTHERN ANOKA COUNTY AS SECONDARY SERVICE AREAS. THE TARGET POPULATION INCLUDES LOW-INCOME COMMUNITIES, BOTH UNINSURED AND THOSE ON MEDICAID. SERVICES WERE PROVIDED AT THREE FREESTANDING CLINICS: FREMONT CLINIC IN NORTH MINNEAPOLIS, CENTRAL AVENUE CLINIC AND SHERIDAN CLINIC IN NORTHEAST MINNEAPOLIS. ON-SITE SERVICES INCLUDE PRIMARY CARE, DISEASE AND CANCER PREVENTION, REPRODUCTIVE AND SEXUAL HEALTH EDUCATING, OB/GYN, CHRONIC DISEASE, INTERPRETING, AND ASSISTANCE WITH HEALTH CARE PLAN ENROLLMENT. WE PROVIDE REFERRALS AND CARE COORDINATION FOR DENTAL, MENTAL HEALTH AND SUBSTANCE ABUSE, HOSPITAL, AND SPECIALTY SERVICES THROUGH PARTNERSHIPS WITH OTHER COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS. NHS PROVIDES A VARIETY OF COMMUNITY HEALTH SERVICES IN SUPPORT OF PRIMARY CARE ACTIVITIES INCLUDING HEALTH EDUCATION, CHRONIC DISEASE PREVENTION, CANCER PREVENTION, AND REPRODUCTIVE HEALTH SERVICES. PHYSICIANS, NURSE PRACTITIONERS, PHYSICIAN ASSISTANTS, CERTIFIED NURSE-MIDWIVES, CLINICAL AND ADMINISTRATIVE SUPPORT STAFF PROVIDE NHS SERVICES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: MENTAL HEALTH:WHILE NHS PROVIDES MENTAL HEALTH CARE SERVICES ON SITE FOR MOST PATIENTS, MENTAL HEALTH CARE SERVICES FOR MEDICARE PATIENTS ARE CURRENTLY AVAILABLE THROUGH OFF-SITE REFERRAL TO NORTHPOINT HEALTH AND WELLNESS CENTER LOCATED IN NORTH MINNEAPOLIS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION PAYS DUES TO THE MINNESOTA ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS (MNACHC). SOME OF THOSE MEMBERSHIP COSTS GO TOWARDS LOBBYING AND ADVOCATING. MNACHC IS A NON-PROFIT MEMBERSHIP ORGANIZATION OF MINNESOTA'S FEDERALLY QUALIFIED HEALTH CENTERS (FQHCS). MNACHC WORKS ON BEHALF OF ITS MEMBERS AND THEIR PATIENTS TO PROMOTE THE COST-EFFECTIVE DELIVERY OF AFFORDABLE, QUALITY PRIMARY HEALTH CARE SERVICES. WITH A SPECIAL EMPHASIS ON MEETING THE NEEDS OF LOW INCOME AND MEDICALLY UNDERSERVED POPULATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FINANCE DIRECTOR AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR REVIEW FORM 990. THE FINANCE DIRECTOR PROVIDES A COPY OF FORM 990 VIA EMAIL WHICH IS REVIEWED THE BY FINANCE COMMITTEE AND THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS PRIOR TO SUBMISSION TO THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANY BOARD MEMBERS HAVING AN INTEREST IN AN ITEM OF BUSINESS PRESENTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS SHALL MAKE PROMPT, FULL AND FRANK DISCLOSURE OF THIS INTEREST PRIOR TO ITS ACTING ON THE ITEM OF BUSINESS. AT THE DISCRETION OF THE BOARD, THE PERSON MAKING THE DECLARATION MAY BE EXCUSED FROM ALL OR A PORTION OF THE RELEVANT DISCUSSION AND VOTING. THE MINUTES OF THE MEETING REFLECT THE DISCLOSURE AND THE VOTING THEREON. THE POLICY IS POSTED ON THE BOARD MEMBER INTRANET AND REVIEWED DURING THE NEW MEMBER ORIENTATION PROCESS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD REVIEWS AND NEGOTIATE WITH POTENTIAL HIRES AND DELIBERATES AND MAKE THE FINAL DECISION FOR THE POSITION OF EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR (CEO). THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR MAKES FINAL DECISIONS REGARDING TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIALS. FOR ALL POSITIONS, SALARY RANGES ARE REVIEWED AND COMPARED TO SALARY SURVEY INFORMATION FOR SIMILAR POSITIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST. THESE DOCUMENTS CAN BE REQUESTED BY CONTACTING THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCE DIRECTOR.
